cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the design of a MAC protocol for LoRaWAN, which is a wireless communication technology for IoT applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a decoding algorithm and uses specific features of the LoRa physical layer, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses system throughput, energy efficiency, and delay, which are related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
